            <bio>
               <p>Dr. Wendy Ashby is Assistant Professor and Academic Specialist for the Division of Technology Integration at the Defense Language Institute Foreign Language Center. Her primary specialization is foreign language faculty and curriculum development. She currently provides vetting and pedagogical expertise to technology-mediated curriculum projects in a number of critical languages. Her teaching background is in German, English as a Second Language, Freshman Composition, and language teaching methodology. Dr. Ashby was awarded a fellowship grant from the US Department of State to conduct English teacher training in Beijing, China and is finishing her sabbatical year there as an independent consultant. While in China, she can be reached privately at <email xlink:href="wendyashby62@yahoo.com">wendyashby62@yahoo.com</email>.</p>
               <p>Wendy Ashby, Division of Technology Integration, Defense Language Institute Foreign Language Center, Presidio of Monterey, Monterey, CA 93944, Email: <email xlink:href="Wendy.Ashby@us.army.mil">Wendy.Ashby@us.army.mil</email>, Web: <uri xlink:href="http://www.dliflc.edu">www.dliflc.edu</uri>
               </p>
